name: Jeffrey Buttle
bio: World champion, Olympic bronze medalist. Figure skater, choreographer.  For choreography requests, please email jeffbuttlechoreography@gmail.com

social_posts.post_text: Such an honour to be in the arena to witness my coach be inducted into the Skate Canada Hall of Fame.  Very few skaters find a coach from the age of 8, and have them by their side when they win Worlds.  I owe my success on the ice to him.  His knowledge, patience (so much patience), and integrity.  Just a few of his qualities that I strive to emulate.  Congrats Lee!
Another wonderful show for Stars on Ice Japan.  Thank you Tyler Myles for all of your help.
After waiting almost two decades, I finally got to hear Mahler’s 5th live!  Absolutely epic.  Full body chills a dozen times. #TSO #torontosymphonyorchestra #mahler
Kicking it old school.  A Good Friday indeed. @nobunari0325 #LeeBarkell
We came, we curled, we lost…fabulously!

Well this happened.  At the age of 40, I’ve decided to go back to University.  I will stay involved on the ice with choreography and coaching but I’ve always wanted to pursue something outside of the rink as well.  Happy to be going back to @uoft
Such a wonderful week working with Ah-sun and Seoyeong!  Two lovely and talented young women.
Can’t describe how fortunate I am to be a part of this tour.  @kb.on.ice has been my idol for my skating life.  He will continue to be.  Tonight was something incredibly special.❤️
